![critical](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/critical.svg)

Similar to `SubmissionRecyclerViewAdapter`, removing `onAttachedToRecyclerView` will cause a crash because the custom `attach` method, which now contains the dependency injection logic, is no longer called automatically. This will result in a `NullPointerException` at runtime. Please reintroduce `onAttachedToRecyclerView` to ensure the adapter is correctly initialized.

```java
    @Override
    public void onAttachedToRecyclerView(@NonNull RecyclerView recyclerView) {
        super.onAttachedToRecyclerView(recyclerView);
        attach(recyclerView.getContext(), recyclerView);
    }

    @Override
    public void attach(Context context, RecyclerView recyclerView) {
        super.attach(context, recyclerView);
        ((MaterialisticApplication) context.getApplicationContext()).applicationComponent.inject(this);
        mLevelIndicatorWidth = AppUtils.getDimensionInDp(mContext, R.dimen.level_indicator_width);
    }
```

